    {
      "title": "[2505.16161] Deep Learning-Driven Ultra-High-Definition Image Restoration: A Survey",
      "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.16161",
      "snippet": "View a PDF of the paper titled Deep Learning-Driven Ultra-High-Definition Image Restoration: A Survey, by Liyan Wang and 5 other authors View PDF HTML (experimental) Abstract: Ultra-high-definition (UHD) image restoration aims to specifically solve the problem of quality degradation in ultra-high-resolution images. Recent advancements in this field are predominantly driven by deep learning-based innovations, including enhancements in dataset construction, network architecture, sampling strategies, prior knowledge integration, and loss functions. In this paper, we systematically review recent progress in UHD image restoration, covering various aspects ranging from dataset construction to algorithm design. This serves as a valuable resource for understanding state-of-the-art developments in the field. We begin by summarizing degradation models for various image restoration subproblems, such as super-resolution, low-light enhancement, deblurring, dehazing, deraining, and desnowing, and em",
